'''Dalata Hotel Group PLC''' is a [[hotel|hotel operator]] with a number of hotels in Ireland and the UK. As of 2018, it is the largest hotel operator in Ireland.<ref name="Indo2016">{{cite web|last1=Cogley|first1=Michael|title=Ireland's largest hotel operator Dalata brings Maldron Hotel brand into England|url=https://www.independent.ie/business/commercial-property/irelands-largest-hotel-operator-dalata-brings-maldron-hotel-brand-into-england-35222824.html|website=The Irish Independent|publisher=The Irish Independent|accessdate=19 April 2018}}</ref>

==History==
Dalata Hotel Group PLC was founded in July 2007 by Pat McCann, former chief executive of the [[The Doyle Collection|Jurys Doyle Hotel Group]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.etoa.org/media/all-news/news-item/new-clayton-hotels-brand-arrives-in-the-uk|title= New Clayton Hotels brand arrives in the UK|publisher=ETOA|accessdate=9 November 2017| date = 26 May 2015}}</ref>

==Hotels==
Hotels operated by Dalata include those in the Maldron Hotels and Clayton Hotels brands.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://dalatahotelgroup.com/our-business/ | title = About - Our Business | accessdate = 4 January 2018 | publisher = Dalata Hotel Group | website = dalatahotelgroup.com | quote = ''Dalata is the largest hotel operator in Ireland [and] operate the Maldron Hotel brand and Clayton Hotel brand throughout Ireland & the UK, as well as managing a portfolio of partner hotels''}}</ref>

Properties operated under the Clayton Hotels brand include the [[Clayton Hotel, Limerick]] (one of the [[List of tallest buildings in Ireland|tallest hotels in Ireland]]),<ref>{{cite web|url = http://dalatahotelgroup.com/hotels/clayton-hotel-limerick/ | publisher = Dalata Hotel Group | title = Clayton Hotel Limerick | accessdate = 12 December 2017 | quote = ''The Clayton Hotel Limerick, Ireland’s tallest hotel, [overlooks the] River Shannon''}}</ref> and the [[Burlington Hotel (Dublin)|Clayton Burlington Hotel, Dublin]] (formerly the Burlington, and now owned by a German real estate group).<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.irishtimes.com/business/commercial-property/germany-s-deka-set-to-check-in-at-gibson-hotel-in-dublin-1.3255505 | publisher = Irish Times | title = Germany's Deka set to check in at Gibson Hotel in Dublin| date = 14 October 2017 | quote = ''Deka [..] owns the former Burlington Hotel in Dublin which is operated by Dalata under the Clayton brand on a 25-year contract''}}</ref> In [[Cork (city)|Cork]], the Clayton Hotel Cork City (formerly the Clarion Hotel), was acquired by the group in 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ihf.ie/content/changing-times-clayton-hotel-cork-city-refurbishment-continues  |title=Changing times at Clayton Hotel Cork City as Refurbishment Continues|publisher = Irish Hotels Federation |date= 11 May 2017 |accessdate=November 9, 2017}}</ref>

