'''Ko Young-tae''' (born 1976) is a South Korean businessman and [[fencing|fencer]]. He competed in the individual and team [[sabre (fencing)|sabre]] events at the [[1998 Asian Games]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Kim |first=H. |date=18 December 1998 |title=이진택 '금 뛰어넘기' |trans-title= |url=http://newslibrary.naver.com/viewer/index.nhn?articleId=1998121800209137004&editNo=45&printCount=1&publishDate=1998-12-18&officeId=00020&pageNo=37&printNo=24069&publishType=00010 |language=ko |newspaper=[[The Dong-a Ilbo]] |location=Seoul |access-date=28 October 2016 }}</ref>
Ko was a close friend of [[Choi Soon-sil]]. Ko is suspected of being involved in the management of The Blue K, Widec Sports, and paper companies. Choi set up these companies in Korea and Germany allegedly to funnel money from the foundations.<ref>{{cite news |last=Kim |first=Bo-eun |date=28 October 2016 |title=Choi Soon-sil 'willing to face investigation' |url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/nation/2016/10/116_217055.html |newspaper=[[The Korea Times]] |location=Seoul |access-date=28 October 2016 }}</ref><ref>https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-38259068</ref><ref>http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/nation/2016/10/116_217091.html</ref>
He became one of the figures in the [[2016 South Korean political scandal]], and has been described as a [[whistleblower]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://graphics.straitstimes.com/STI/STIMEDIA/Interactives/2017/03/south-korea-scandal/ko-young-tae.html|title=The ‘toy-boy’-turned-whistle-blower: Ko Young Tae|work=The Straits Times|access-date=2017-03-21|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-38259068|title=Park Geun-hye impeached: Did a puppy bring down South Korea's president?|date=2016-12-09|work=BBC News|access-date=2017-03-21|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/12/09/world/asia/park-geun-hye-puppy.html|title=Key Figure in South Korean Leader’s Troubles: A Puppy|last=Sang-hun|first=Choe|date=2016-12-09|work=The New York Times|access-date=2017-03-21|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> He disclosed a documentary showing that his neighbors tried to steal the money from the Mir and the Blue K Foundation by using Choi Soon Shin.
