'''Ozii Obiyo''' (born January 23, 1985) is a Nigerian-American entrepreneur from [[Arlington, Texas]]. As a promise to his brother Chuki Obiyo, when they were both students at the [[University of Texas at Austin]], he started the first online African Radio show in [[Austin, Texas]] on [[KVRX]] called African Extravaganza.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://pioneer.csueastbay.edu/PioneerWeb/PioneerNews6-25-09/PioneerNews6-25-09-Page6.pdf|title= Producer Has Switched From A Career in Diplomacy to Short Film|accessdate= 2010-02-19|last=Qudus|
first=Kemi|date=2007-10-30|publisher= The Pioneer}}</ref> Started in 2005, the show showcased a variety of African artists representing different genres and cultures, from [[Fela Kuti]] and his [[Afrobeat]] to [[Angelique Kidjo]] and her [[Afro pop music|Afropop]].<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.nlnshop.com/radioshow.html|title= Ozii Obiyo presents...|accessdate= 2010-01-11|publisher= Africa In the News by NLN}}</ref> The fusion of cultures on his show was an experience that Ozii coined as "Afro-fantastic".<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.dtweekend.com/issues/20060223/staffpicks.html|title= AfroFantastik!|accessdate= 2006-02-23|last=Ramirez|
first=Ramon|date=2007-10-30|publisher= The Daily Texan}}</ref> The radio show led to AfroFantasticTV, a TV show that interviewed students and small business owners on the streets of Austin about African culture through humor.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://africaneed.com/afrofantastic-tv-episode-1-intro-to-africa|title= Intro to Africa|accessdate= 2010-01-11|publisher= AfricaNEED}}</ref> The TV show, broadcast on [[K29HW-D|K09VR]], featured Texas business owners discussing how different cultural aspects of [[Sub-Saharan Africa]] connected to the [[Keep Austin Weird]] business campaign; in one episode, the show featured [[Mark Cuban]], owner of the [[Dallas Mavericks]].<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.nlnshop.com/afrofantasticTV.html |title= Mark Cuban on AfroFantasticTV|accessdate= 2007-03-11|publisher= Africa In The News by NLN}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.texasstudenttv.com/schedule_friday.html |title= Programs on Texas Student Television: Cable Channel 16 |accessdate= 2006-10-10|publisher= Texas Student Television}}</ref> As of March 2010, Ozii, through Mediasify, LLC is producing web TV shows, videos, and press releases for business owners.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.i-newswire.com/mediasify-joins-dallas-regional/26227|title= Mediasify Joins Dallas Regional Chamber to Assist Professionals in Marketing Their Expertise|accessdate= 2010-03-12|last=CCO|date=2009-12-30|publisher= i-Newswire}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://myafricanplan.com/2011/01/mediasify-yourself|title= Spotlight on Mediasify by Chuki Obiyo of My African Plan|accessdate= 2011-12-01|last=CCO|date=2011-12-01|publisher= My African Plan}}</ref>

