'''Thomas Zilliacus''' is a Co-Founder of [[Yuuzoo]] Corporation Limited, Chairman of [[Miss Supertalent]] and former CEO of Nokia Asia Pacific.<ref name="bloomberg">{{cite news|title=Thomas Henrik Zilliacus M.Sc. Econ.|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=8633138&privcapId=45239767|date=5 September 2013|accessdate=29 October 2015|publisher=''bloomberg.com''}}</ref>
==Biography== Zilliacus holds a Master of Science in Economics and Business Administration from [[Hanken School of Economics]], Helsinki.<ref name="sias/">{{cite news|title=Si2i Limited - Securities Investors Association (Singapore)|url=https://sias.org.sg/index9.php?handler=ir&action=ir_content&ir_content_title_id=1705|date=29 October 2015|accessdate=29 October 2015|publisher=''sias.org.sg/''}}</ref> He is the founder of Mobile FutureWorks, Inc.,<ref name="ZDNet">{{cite news|title=Nokia is dead, Newkia rises from its ashes|url=http://www.zdnet.com/article/nokia-is-dead-newkia-rises-from-its-ashes/|date=22 September 2014|accessdate=5 September 2014|publisher=''zdnet.com''}}</ref> and serves as a Senior Adviser to several companies in the wireless space.{{citation needed|date=October 2015}} Prior to Mobile FutureWorks, he held various senior management positions with Finnish leading mobile handset company [[Nokia]] including serving as Regional Director of Asia-Pacific region at Nokia Southeast Asia Pte Ltd.<ref name="TechinAsia.com">{{cite news|title=Interview: the man who led Nokia’s charge into Asia|url=https://www.techinasia.com/interview-man-led-nokias-charge-asia/|date=27 January 2014|accessdate=29 October 2015|publisher=''techinasia.com''}}</ref><ref name="SPH Magazines">{{cite news|title=What Newkia's Chairman Thinks About Nokia's Android Phones, Xiaomi & Stephen Elop|url=http://www.hardwarezone.com.sg/tech-news-what-newkias-chairman-thinks-about-nokias-android-phones-xiaomi-stephen-elop|date=3 March 2014|accessdate=29 October 2015|publisher=''hardwarezone.com.sg/'}}</ref> He serves as the Chairman of OpenMobile Corporation and Mobile Brands Corporation.<ref name="MobileTechNews.com">{{cite news|title=Open Mobile receives funding from Wellington Partnersl=http://www.mobiletechnews.com/info/2000/07/03/095902.html|date=3 July 2000|publisher=''mobiletechnews.com''}}</ref><ref name="Mis Asia">{{cite news|title=MIS-Asia - Nokia is dead, Newkia is born|url=http://mis-asia.com/tech/mobile-and-wireless/nokia-is-dead-newkia-is-born/|date=4 September 2014|accessdate=29 October 2015|publisher=''mis-asia.com''}}</ref> and Independent Non-Executive Director of S i2i Limited (formerly, Spice i2i Ltd), serves as a Member of Advisory Board at Scanbuy invited by its founder Olivier Attia, Director of S Mobility Limited (now Spice Mobility Limited [[Spice Digital]] company )<ref name="s-i2i/">{{cite news|title=Board of Directors - Si2i Limited - MediaRing|url=http://www.s-i2i.com/board-of-directors.html|date=29 October 2015|accessdate=29 October 2015|publisher=''s-i2i.com/''}}</ref><ref name="zonebourse">{{cite news|title=S i2i Ltd : Actionnaires, dirigeants et description métier {{!}} MZZ ..|url=http://www.zonebourse.com/S-I2I-LTD-441771/societe/|date=29 October 2014|accessdate=29 October 2015|publisher=''zonebourse.com'' |language=fr}}</ref> He served as an Additional Director of [[Wall Street]] Finance Ltd.<ref name="business-standard">{{cite news|title=Sudip Bandyopadhyay, new Addnl Dir of Wall Street Finance|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/sudip-bandyopadhyay-new-addnl-dir-of-wall-street-finance-109113000178_1.html|date=30 November 2009|accessdate=29 October 2015|publisher=''business-standard.com''}}</ref> and a Co-Founder and First Chairman of mobile services industry body, the Mobile Entertainment Forum.{{citation needed|date=October 2015}}
